sys_update_xml.name: sys_ws_operation_e12397510fca160035f2ab78b1050e9c
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl/><http_method>POST</http_method><name>results</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {

    // implement resource here

    gs.log("Starting Jenkins import");
    var job = request.body.data.job;
    var build_number = request.body.data.build_number;
    var build_status = request.body.data.status;
    var console = request.body.data.console;
    var url = request.body.data.url;
    var revision = request.body.data.revision;
    var duration = request.body.data.duration;
    var pass_count = request.body.data.pass_count;
    var fail_count = request.body.data.fail_count;
    var skipped_count = request.body.data.skip_count;

    // Create the u_build record
    var buildGr = new GlideRecord('u_automated_build');
    buildGr.u_job = job;
    buildGr.u_build = build_number;
    buildGr.u_console = console;
    buildGr.u_status = build_status;
    buildGr.u_scm_revision = revision;
    buildGr.u_duration = duration;
    buildGr.u_url = url;
    buildGr.u_pass_count = pass_count;
    buildGr.u_fail_count = fail_count;
    buildGr.u_skipped_count = skipped_count;
    var buildGrSysId = buildGr.insert();

    // Create the u_automated_test records
    // (and create other supporting records if they aren't present)
    var results = request.body.data.results;

    for (var i=0; i<results.length; i++) {

        var testedTaskGrSysId = undefined;
        var testCaseName = results[i].test_case;
        if (testCaseName.indexOf("STRY") > -1) {
            var regex = /STRY(\d+)/
            var numberArr = testCaseName.match(regex);
            var number = numberArr[0];

            var taskGr = new GlideRecord('task');
            if (taskGr.get('number', number)) {
                gs.log("FOUND A TESTED TASK: " + taskGr.number);
                testedTaskGrSysId = taskGr.sys_id;
            }
        }

        // Test for a matching Test Case, create one if not exists
        var testCaseSysId;
        var testCaseGr = new GlideRecord('tm_test_case');
        testCaseGr.addQuery('short_description', testCaseName);
        testCaseGr.query();
        if (!testCaseGr.next()) {

            testCaseGr = new GlideRecord('tm_test_case');
            testCaseGr.short_description = testCaseName;
            testCaseGr.prereq = "Automated Test Case";
            testCaseSysId = testCaseGr.insert();
        } else {
            testCaseSysId = testCaseGr.sys_id;
        }
		
		if (testedTaskGrSysId) {
			// Create the m2m record between Test Case and Task
			var testCaseM2MGr = new GlideRecord('u_m2m_tasks_test_cases');
			testCaseM2MGr.u_task = testedTaskGrSysId;
			testCaseM2MGr.u_test_case = testCaseSysId;
			testCaseM2MGr.insert();
		}

        // Test for a matching Test, create one if not exists
        var testSysId;
        var testGr = new GlideRecord('tm_test');
        testGr.addQuery('tm_test_case', testCaseSysId);
        testGr.addQuery('test', results[i].name);
        testGr.query();
        if (!testGr.next()) {

            testGr = new GlideRecord('tm_test');
            testGr.tm_test_case = testCaseSysId;
            testGr.test = results[i].name;
            testSysId = testGr.insert();
        } else {
            testSysId = testGr.sys_id;
        }

        // Test for a matching Test Case Instance
        var testCaseInstanceSysId;
        var testCaseInstanceGr = new GlideRecord('u_automated_test_case');
        var key = results[i].test_case + ' (Build: ' + build_number + ')';
        testCaseInstanceGr.addQuery('short_description', key);
        testCaseInstanceGr.query();
        if (!testCaseInstanceGr.next()) {

            testCaseInstanceGr = new GlideRecord('u_automated_test_case');
            testCaseInstanceGr.short_description = key;
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_scm_revision = revision;
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_url = url;
            testCaseInstanceGr.execution_status = 'passed';
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_pass_count = 0;
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_fail_count = 0;
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_skipped_count = 0;
            testCaseInstanceGr.u_build = buildGrSysId;
            if (testedTaskGrSysId)
                testCaseInstanceGr.u_tested_task = testedTaskGrSysId;
            testCaseInstanceSysId = testCaseInstanceGr.insert();

        } else {
            testCaseInstanceSysId = testCaseInstanceGr.sys_id;
        }
		
		if (testedTaskGrSysId) {
			// Create the m2m record between Test Case and Task
			var testCaseInstanceM2MGr = new GlideRecord('u_m2m_tasks_test_case_instances');
			testCaseInstanceM2MGr.u_task = testedTaskGrSysId;
			testCaseInstanceM2MGr.u_test_case = testCaseInstanceSysId;
			testCaseInstanceM2MGr.insert();
		}

        // Create the Test Instance, linking it to the Test Case
        var automatedTestGr = new GlideRecord('u_automated_test');
        automatedTestGr.test = results[i].name;
        automatedTestGr.tm_test_case_instance = testCaseInstanceSysId;
        automatedTestGr.actual_result = results[i].error_details;
        automatedTestGr.u_stacktrace = results[i].error_stack_trace;

        switch(results[i].status) {
            case "PASSED":
                automatedTestGr.execution_status = 'passed';
                testCaseInstanceGr.u_pass_count = parseInt(testCaseInstanceGr.u_pass_count)+1;
                break;
            case "FAILED":
                automatedTestGr.execution_status = 'failed';
                testCaseInstanceGr.execution_status = 'failed';
                testCaseInstanceGr.u_fail_count = parseInt(testCaseInstanceGr.u_fail_count)+1;
                break;
            case "REGRESSION":
                automatedTestGr.execution_status = 'failed';
                testCaseInstanceGr.execution_status = 'failed';
                testCaseInstanceGr.u_fail_count = parseInt(testCaseInstanceGr.u_fail_count)+1;
                break;
        }

        automatedTestGr.insert();
        testCaseInstanceGr.update();

    }

})(request, response);]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/snc/jenkinsimport/results</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/results</relative_path><request_example/><requires_acl_authorization>false</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>true</requires_authentication><short_description/><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin_SHARE_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-08 12:21:17</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>e12397510fca160035f2ab78b1050e9c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>results</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_e12397510fca160035f2ab78b1050e9c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin_SHARE_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-08 12:45:29</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="JenkinsImport">4c0357510fca160035f2ab78b1050e38</web_service_definition><web_service_version/></sys_ws_operation></record_update>
